<subSubSection pageId="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[707,1193,194,667]" pageId="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,845,593,614]" pageId="15">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from 
<emphasis box="[707,801,619,640]" italics="true" pageId="15">apolegma</emphasis>
(= hem of a robe), a Greek noun, and refers to the widened epipleural fold.
</paragraph>
